#########
# Intro #
#########

Just what one would expect from languages with comments.
The one special bit is nesting multiline comments, similar to racket or rust.

Note the use of '#'.
I do like '//', but I also like integer division syntax, so '#' it is.

############
# Examples #
############

--via
# Simple comments

/*
    Multiline comment.
    /*
        Nested multiline comment!
    */ 
*/

# Some edge cases:
#
/**/
/* */
/****/
--

